From: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2015 18:37:50 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1865/2066] dmaengine: rcar-dmac: Use DECLARE_BITMAP

upstream 08acf38e3615a5cf641d84f815f3f3ebd2953243 commit

Use the generic mechanism to declare a bitmap instead of unsigned long.

Signed-off-by: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Signed-off-by: Vinod Koul <vinod.koul@intel.com>
---
 drivers/dma/sh/rcar-dmac.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/dma/sh/rcar-dmac.c b/drivers/dma/sh/rcar-dmac.c
index 84511f7..c296a37 100644
--- a/drivers/dma/sh/rcar-dmac.c
+++ b/drivers/dma/sh/rcar-dmac.c
@@ -202,7 +202,7 @@ struct rcar_dmac {
 	unsigned int n_channels;
 	struct rcar_dmac_chan *channels;
 
-	unsigned long modules[256 / BITS_PER_LONG];
+	DECLARE_BITMAP(modules, 256);
 };
 
 #define to_rcar_dmac(d)		container_of(d, struct rcar_dmac, engine)
